         <abstract>
            <p>We prove the analyticity (uniform in h) of the semigroups generated on L&lt;sub&gt;p&lt;/sub&gt; (0, 1), 1 ≤ p ≤ ∞, by finite element analogues A&lt;sub&gt;h&lt;/sub&gt; of a one-dimensional second-order elliptic operator A under Dirichlet boundary conditions. This is accomplished by showing the appropriate estimates for the resolvents by means of energy arguments. The results are applied to prove stability and optimal-order error bounds for numerical solutions of the associated parabolic problem for both smooth and nonsmooth data.</p>
          </abstract>
